Our project researcher, Prof. Teemu Roos, will take part in a major Nobel debate on how machine learning and award-winning physics researchers are connected.  <a href="https://acadsci.fi/ajankohtaista/tapahtumat/suuri-nobel-keskustelu-24-10-2024/">https://acadsci.fi/ajankohtaista/tapahtumat/suuri-nobel-keskustelu-24-10-2024/</a><br/>---<br/>The Great Nobel Debate, 24.10.2024<br/><br/><strong>Time: </strong>24.10. 17.00-18.30<br/><strong>Venue:</strong> Sanomatalo Mediatorium (Töölönlahdenkatu 2, 00100 Helsinki)<br/><br/>Welcome to hear about Nobel Prize-winning research! Finnish experts tell us which research in medicine, physics, chemistry and economics won awards this autumn, with Director <strong>Mika Maliranta</strong>, Professor <strong>Antti Poso</strong>, Professor <strong>Teemu Roos</strong> and Research Director <strong>Sanna Vuoristo</strong>. Hosted by science journalists <strong>Mari Heikkilä</strong> and <strong>Matti Mielonen</strong><br/><br/><em>The event is organised by Helsingin Sanomat, the Finnish Association of Science Journalists, the Finnish Academy of Science, Finska Vetenskaps-Societeten - Suomen Tiedeseura, the Academy of Science, Svenska tekniska vetenskapsakademien i Finland and the Finnish Academies of Science Cooperation Council.</em>
